    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Deck your opponent, then either speed ahead of him or whomp on him until he submits! This deck has the alternate victory condition of corrupting the Ringbearer; I think it&#39;s entirely possible, given some of these combos. <br />
<br />
Go second, don&#39;t bid a thing. It doesn&#39;t matter if your opponent gets Aragorn out; in fact, you want someone out there that will stick around for the good fight with three or four DDotRs on them and Toldea having them assign :) (3 DDotRs + Toldea&#39;s first skirmish: 6 cards gone from hand + 1 burden; fierce skirmish = another 3 burdens). Uruk Rager with Sword and Rampage can get rid of another six cards. Each Desperate Measures is good for five, Nobody Tosses can be played in multiples, if you have &#39;em. (which you hopefully will using Grimir) Deny their hand with White Arrows, Mirror, Orc Inquisitor and Tower Lieutenant (save the Enheartened Foes for him). <br />
<br />
I&#39;m highly considering putting in a couple of copies of Irresistable Shadow in; keep this in mind while trimming. I think it would be worthwhile if the deck works the way it should. :) <br />
